caption: Been going to China night since 2015. Both because of tradition and because I love their food. The portions are big and the food is fantastic. I have a habit of always getting the same thing, but it never disappointed. Its my favorite Chinese food place.

The rice was nasty and mushy. The orange chicken was too soggy.  Never again!

Typical American Chinese fare, decent pricing and lunch specials.  #23 Chicken Wings lunch special - The wings were okay, not bad but not memorable either. The included shrimp fried rice was standard. Getting it spicy made it better. Also includes pop and egg roll.  Dan Dan Noodle - Not the the Sichuan style I was expecting. Doesn't have that numbing spiciness. Noodles were very soft. Just chicken and peanuts with a little bit of spice. Wouldn't order again.
I love the sweet and sour chicken! Their dinner combo is a great deal too.
I love this place very much. there is a different mood. The cuisine is great. the service is effective and the team is trained. The pay is honest. I highly recommend.

This restaurant is my favored. I go to plenty of restaurants but to this place I  constantly return again and again. The stuff is very cordial and the cooking they offer is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a nice dinner in this place. Highly recommended.

two days ago was the first time we went to this magnificent restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last time. We had great time with the generous service, with the finest  meal and fine drinks and with the modest pay. We will absolutely come back in a short time.

Had a quick stop over here with my wife coz we were really hungry and still had a long drive home and i must say the food was awesome. I almost ate my plate lol. Had the sweet and sour chicken while my wife had another delicacy.  Above all We didnt regret our stop here.
Would surely recommend trying out this place. Awesome character, delicious dishes, excellent customer service. They never disappoint.

Szechuan chicken was decent, said it was supposed to be spicy but was not at all. The pepper steak was atrocious, the "steak" didnt even feel like steak and the sauce was flavorless and gelatinous. The food is pretty good, especially in terms of taste, quantity and price. The staff are courteous and pleasant. My go-tos are the Hot & Sour Soup and the Kung Bao Chicken Fried Rice. I'm almost a regular here now!

The absolute best place to get a hugeeeee amount if Chinese food. The rice is literally over flowing. You will have delicious food for days! Singapore rice noodles and Mongolian chicken is my favorite. May not be the prettiest inside but the best for late night food at home!

I love China Knight!!! It's such a good family oriented business.  Their delivery system is amazing!!! They are super fast and accurate every time. The food is delicious, too. The restaurant specializes in great food and affordable prices.
Excellent Beef Fried Rice and when tasted my Wife's Sweet & Sour Chicken..... OMG it was soooo fresh and tasty. Good food.

I've been going to China night Cafe for 3 years now about every other week during the school year. I've never been disappointed with the quality of the food or the service. It's hard to beat their lunch special! They've recently remodeled the place and it looks really nice!

Haven't eaten here in about 30 years (since my dad worked at the University) and had to stop in. The food is still delicious, and a great value! The lunch special comes with shrimp fried rice, vegetable egg roll, entree and a soda (or bottled water) for $7. I tried to resist eating the whole plate, but succumbed. Try it!

I live right across from here. They have great service and the counter staff is always friendly. They recently renovated so the interiors are slightly nicer.  The food is pretty good considering the price. I've had their lunch options. Orange chicken and sesame chicken are a definite must try. If you don't like a fish flavor in your rice tell them because they add shrimp sauce to the fried rice.  The egg rolls are damn good too. Excellent choice for college kids.
Cheap and tasty

I have been going to this place for over 20 yrs. I came all the way from Urbana Illinois to come here today, and it is worth every mile i drove. I love this place.
The place is very good for students.

This is definitely not the best place for Chinese, but a cool place for dinner and hang out by Taylor street. If you are hungry at the school and looking for quick simple food, you got this one. Open till 9pm. We ordered Crabmeat Rangoon for starter and trust me it was one of the best appetizers I had recently: filled with crab and shrimp and the taste was so refreshing. Like most of the Chinese restaurants, the main dishes come with steamed rice. We ordered Szechwan Chicken, Hot Pepper Chicken and Kung Bao Pork. All of the item was simple and delicious no doubt. The amount was very filling (being a skinny guy, I shouldn't make myself as reference, but I had to take out the rest of the food and it took 2 more days to finish. I ordered large though)  Good food for reasonable price. Probably will be back again

This little gem is hidden in the middle of a UIC block. You probably won't want to dine in, but the food is great. They make great fried rice, egg rolls, and other traditional Chinese dishes. They staff is very nice, but they often times have a hard time understanding me.
